DS2010_Celtics_Data <- read.csv("DS2010_Celtics_Data.csv")
dataB <- DS2010_Celtics_Data

Data Engineering

#Taking out redundant columns
dataB <- dataB[, -c(1, 3, 5, 25:41)]
# Making win(1) or loss(0) ---- 1 or 0
dataB$WL <- ifelse(dataB$WL == "W", 1, 0)
# Making X column "HomeAway" into 1 or 0 ---- home(1) / away(0)
colnames(dataB)[2] <- "HomeAway"

dataB$HomeAway <- ifelse(dataB$HomeAway == "@", 0, 1)

#The tree library
